The actual request handling logic lives in the imported modules (invoiceRoutes, clientRoutes, userRoutes, profile), not in this file.
- The direct endpoints defined in this file are:

  - POST /create-pdf → anonymous function

- All identified entries have path strings defined as literal strings in the source, and the relevant prefixes indicate they are path prefixes rather than full concrete paths (where applicable).
- All entries are part of a RESTful API pattern (standard HTTP methods on resources or resource-like endpoints). None are marked as test-only.
- None of the entries rely on path parameters in curly braces in this file.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
